<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="13" pageNumber="124" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1853,2022]" box="[199,1436,1997,2022]" pageId="13" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1997,2022]" pageId="13" pageNumber="124">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Melander, A. L." box="[324,514,1997,2022]" pageId="13" pageNumber="124" pagination="183 - 221" refId="ref18406" refString="Melander, A. L. (1918) The dipterous genus Drapetis Meigen (Family Empididae). Annals of Entomological Society of America, 11: 183 - 221." type="journal article" year="1918">Melander (1918)</bibRefCitation>
originally distinguished 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melander" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[800,961,1998,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pennescens">
<emphasis box="[800,961,1998,2021]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="124">C. pennescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[1035,1159,1998,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armipes">
<emphasis box="[1035,1159,1998,2021]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="124">C. armipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the color of the legs
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,467]" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">
being blacker, hind femur bearing a single subapical anteroventral seta, ventral hair-like bristles on hind tibia, hind tarsomere 1 blackish lacking golden pruinescence, and wings hyaline. However, the species are actually very similar, because the color of the legs is quite similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[804,929,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armipes">
<emphasis box="[804,929,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">C. armipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[949,969,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">cf</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation box="[987,1075,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–11" captionStartId="9.[151,264,683,705]" captionTargetBox="[154,1387,199,662]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,662]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 10–11. Crossopalpus armipes (Bezzi, 1909) (Holotype ♀, SMTD). 10. Lateral habitus; 11. Labels. Scale bar = 0.5 mm. Figures kindly provided by Uwe Kallweit, from Senckenberg Museum für Tierkunde Dresden (SMTD)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626752/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1090,1165,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[168,1402,209,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[168,1402,209,1682]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Crossopalpus pennescens (Melander, 1918) (Holotype ♀, NMNH). 16. Lateral habitus; 17. Frontal habitus; 18. Dorsal habitus; 19. Labels. Scale bars = 0.5mm. Figures kindly provided by Alyssa Seemann, National Museum of Natural History (NMNH), Smithsonian Institution." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626756/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">16, 17</figureCitation>
), and the color of hind tarsomere 1 is similar in several South American species (e.g., 
<figureCitation box="[853,982,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1781]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Crossopalpus Bigot. Male habitus. 23–24. Crossopalpus albivertex sp. nov. (Holotype ♂, CZMA); 23. Lateral view; 24. Dorsal view; 25–26. Crossopalpus aliceae sp. nov. (Holotype ♂, INPA). 25. Lateral view; 26. Dorsal view; 27–28. Crossopalpus goliathus sp. nov. (Holotype ♂, CZMA); 27. Lateral view; 28. Dorsal view; 29–30. Crossopalpus xanthogaster sp. nov. (Holotype ♂, INPA); 29. Lateral view; 30. Dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626760/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">Figs 25, 27</figureCitation>
). The ventral hair-like bristles are absent only in 
<taxonomicName authority="Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[237,351,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aliceae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[237,351,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">C. aliceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[358,448,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[358,448,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and present in 
<taxonomicName box="[628,751,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armipes">
<emphasis box="[628,751,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">C. armipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rafael, J. A." box="[959,1118,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" pagination="733 - 739" refId="ref18805" refString="Rafael, J. A. (1995) Revisao das especies Neotropicais de Empididae (Diptera) descritas por Mario Bezzi. II. Tachydromiinae. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 39, 733 - 739." type="journal article" year="1995">Rafael (1995)</bibRefCitation>
. Additionally, the scutum of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,274,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armipes">
<emphasis box="[151,274,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">C. armipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Melander" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[331,492,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pennescens">
<emphasis box="[331,492,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">C. pennescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears numerous rows of bristles, a character shared only with 
<taxonomicName authority="Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[1200,1338,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goliathus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1200,1338,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">C. goliathus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,332,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,332,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in South America. 
<taxonomicName box="[365,616,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armipes">
<emphasis box="[365,616,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">Crossopalpus armipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from the other two species mainly by the presence of tomentum on upper 1/2 of the postocular area, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[740,764,419,433]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[847,855,419,433]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">1</subScript>
very sinuous and parallel, similar to the Palearctic species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zetterstedt)" authorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[239,542,442,467]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvinervis">
<emphasis box="[239,397,443,467]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">C. curvinervis</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kovalev." authorityName="Kovalev." box="[597,820,442,467]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Crossopalpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abditus">
<emphasis box="[597,713,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="125">C. abditus</emphasis>
Kovalev.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
